IF WE GO BACK TO THE SHIP

385
00:21:21,708 --> 00:21:23,750
AND RUN A MORE DETAILED
SCAN OF THE AREA.

386
00:21:23,833 --> 00:21:26,208
- BUT YOU'RE SURE SHE'S
SOMEWHERE AROUND HERE, RIGHT?

387
00:21:26,291 --> 00:21:30,000
- YEAH. ACCORDING TO
MY CALCULATIONS, AT LEAST.

388
00:21:30,083 --> 00:21:32,208
- I STILL GOT PLENTY
OF OXYGEN HERE.

389
00:21:32,291 --> 00:21:34,333
YOU GO ON BACK.
I'LL KEEP LOOKING.

390
00:21:34,416 --> 00:21:36,083
- ( woman humming )

391
00:21:36,166 --> 00:21:37,958
- ROY, WAIT. LISTEN.
YOU HEAR THAT?

392
00:21:40,041 --> 00:21:42,833
IS THAT SINGING?

393
00:21:44,583 --> 00:21:46,041
- THAT SOUNDS LIKE...

394
00:21:46,125 --> 00:21:48,333
- ( woman humming )

395
00:21:57,125 --> 00:21:59,416
- Roy: SILLY GIRL.

396
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:04,083
YOU WERE TAKING SO DAMN LONG,
I DECIDED TO COME AND GET YOU.

397
00:22:06,958 --> 00:22:08,041
( crying ) SOLTY!

398
00:22:11,833 --> 00:22:12,875
LET'S GO HOME.

399
00:22:17,291 --> 00:22:18,375
- ROY?

400
00:22:23,666 --> 00:22:26,166
LET'S...

